rComments: I found Prof. Ferguson to be incredibly passionate about the Romantic period in France and highly knowledgeable on Balzac and the Romantics. Overall, it was never boring in class and weekly lectures were always eloquently delivered in a skillful and elegant manner. I highly recommend this course to all interested in art, literature, and music.
An absolutely amazing professor. I have him to thank for my obsession with Balzac!

He is incredibly elequoent, if you delve on what he says you'll never find the material dry. The class is impressive although drawing on major themes and inter-textual themes would make it incredible.

Prof is sometimes humourous and his sarcasm made the course better. However, lectures were really boring and dry. Every class we'd go through every page or line & cover alot of surface stuff. More analysis on major themes!! Alot of the time we could never finish texts & had to rush and skip alot!!

I don't know what that other dude was talking about.  You obviously think you know more about this course that the prof does if you are so bored. He does a lot more than just read passages from the book, you haven't been listening if you that's your impression. He's a GREAT prof

I found his lectures boring. He spends most of the class time re-reading the passages to us rather than speaking about specific topics/themes/etc. We did not go into depth with anything and he allowed people in class to continuously interrupt with inane comments. He is always cheerful & jokes a lot.

This is the BEST Western literature course ever, all because of Prof. Ferguson! He is very enthusiasitc about the literature studied, and is always highly entertaining and humourous! He is definitely the greatest English prof. I've ever had!
